# Tree-sitter grammar mappings for MC editor syntax highlighting
#
# Format:
#   file           <filename_regex>   <grammar_name> <display_name>
#   shebang        <first_line_regex> <grammar_name> <display_name>
#   inject         <parent_grammar>   <child_grammar> <node_type1>,<node_type2>,...
#   inject_dynamic <parent_grammar>   <block_node> <lang_node> <content_node>
#
# The grammar_name is used to look up:
#   - Static registry function: tree_sitter_<name>()
#   - Query file:               <name>-highlights.scm (in queries/ dir)
#
# Static injection (inject):
#   Runs a secondary parser on byte ranges of specific node types from
#   the parent tree. The child grammar's highlights override the parent's.
#   Node types support "parent/child" syntax (e.g. "script_element/raw_text").
#   Example: inject markdown markdown_inline inline,pipe_table_cell
#
# Dynamic injection (inject_dynamic):
#   For code blocks where the language varies per block. Reads the language
#   name from <lang_node> and parses <content_node> with the matching grammar.
#   Example: inject_dynamic markdown fenced_code_block info_string code_fence_content
#
# To add a new language:
#   1. Vendor the grammar sources in src/editor/ts-grammars/<name>/
#   2. Add the entry to ts-grammar-registry.h
#   3. Place a <name>-highlights.scm file in the queries/ directory
#   4. Add a "file" and/or "shebang" line here

file \.(adb|ads|ada)$ ada Ada\ Program
file \.(s|S|asm)$ asm Assembly
file \.(awk|gawk|mawk)$ awk AWK\ Program
file \.(sh|bash|zsh|PKGBUILD|\.bashrc|\.bash_profile|\.profile)$ bash Shell\ Script
